Just a reminder for all Sentinel staff and students to perform health screenings each morning. These screenings help us keep everyone as healthy as possible.

Remember to wash your cloth masks regularly with warm water & soap or in your washing machine. Do not place in a dryer. Please allow masks to air dry.

SPS would ask that students not wear masks that have one way valves on them. If you wear a mask, please wear a solid mask or face covering without any valves.

Parents will be asked to screen students before bringing them to school or putting them on the bus each morning. The screening process will consist of a few basic health questions and taking a temperature reading. The health questions to be answered will be provided to families. We believe this process can be done successfully each morning, only taking 15-30 seconds per student to complete.

All Sentinel staff will self screen each morning before coming to work. The screening process for staff will be the same as students.

It's very important to remember daily health screenings for students.
Refrigerator magnets will be sent home with families soon.

post_text:
July 8, 2020

Dear Sentinel students and parents,

As many of you read this, I‚Äôm sure you are wondering about the back to school plans for students at Sentinel Public Schools. We are in the final stages of editing and revising our plan. We started our planning process at the end of May and our goal was to have a plan in place that we could send out to parents and students by the middle of July. We are still on pace to meet those goals. I am hopeful that by this time next week, you will be looking at or will have already read our back to school plan. I can tell you that we have every intention of beginning with students in the school buildings on August 13. Our goal will be to have traditional in-person school as much as is possible and safe for our students and staff in the 2020-2021 school year.

We appreciate your patience as we try to make decisions that maximize learning and safety for all our school community.

Sincerely,
Mr. Goostree

Our last day for meals will be FRIDAY, JUNE 26. Meals for kids up to 18 years old may be picked up in front of the gym lobby from 8:30-9:30AM on the dates listed below.

Mr. Goostree would like to thank Deyanira Barrera, Yolanda Silva, Sylvia Martinez, Glenette Carlson, Paula Combs and Theron Graybill. These employees have been directly involved with preparing, packaging, serving and delivering all of the meals that we have offered since March 26. Their willingness to make sure that our children were fed in Sentinel, Rocky, Retrop and Carter has been extremely remarkable. We hope this food service opportunity has lifted some of the burden from parents as they have navigated through the last few months. We appreciate all of the participation from our community and your diligence in keeping your kids healthy during this time.

If your student was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma‚Äôs Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income.

The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020 deadline at https://secure.okcollegestart.org/applications/Oklahoma_Promise/apply.html. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

post_text:
Testive is offering free online proctored practice SATs/ACTs tests every Wednesday and Saturday through the summer.

Testive's weekly online practice tests emulate the experience of an official SAT or ACT to give students an incredibly productive prep experience. The online tests are supported by a Testive Student Advisor, run a full 3 hours (just like the real exams) and can be done from the comfort and safety of home. And scores are given immediately after the test is completed.

Parents can register via this link: https://www.testive.com/free-practice-test/

Dear Parents, Students, Staff and Community Members,
We are still working on our meal delivery system for the weeks of March 23 and March 30. We are waiting to get a few more pieces of information from the state and federal government. I will send out an update on Thursday, March 19 with more details about student meals during this school closure.

Questions that have come up in the last 24 hours:
Will students have to make up these school days?
Will students still participate in state and federal testing after the school closure?

We don‚Äôt currently have answers to these questions. These are being discussed at the state and federal level and we hope to have more information on these topics by March 26.

You can find more information and stay up to date on the Oklahoma State Department of Education‚Äôs website at:
https://sde.ok.gov

You can also find more information at the Oklahoma State Department of Health‚Äôs website at:
https://coronavirus.health.ok.gov

Sincerely,

Mr. Goostree

Our school will be sending BOX TOPS FOR EDUCATION in on Feb. 26. You can help us reach our yearly goal and make our earnings check BIG by sending in your Box Tops this month. If you have Box Tops you still need to submit, here are some optional tips that‚Äôll make the submission process easier:
1.) Bundle your Box Tops in groups of 10 or 50 using a sealable bag or envelope.
2.) Tape or glue Box Tops on a collection sheet, available at BTFE.com.
3.) Send a Ziplock bag filled with Box Tops to school or mail them to PO Box 640, Sentinel, OK 73664.
4.) You may submit digital Box Tops through the app at anytime to be credited to MCMURRAY ELEMENTARY.
Once we send in all our Box Tops, our school will receive a check from Box Tops for Education. If you have any questions, feel free to contact kfunkhouser@sentinel.k12.ok.us OR call 580-393-4742.
Thanks for your help this school year!

We would like to invite you to the 75th Annual Sentinel Jr. Livestock Show to be held on Tuesday, February 4, 2020 at the Sentinel Area Activity Center. The show will begin at 10AM with the show order of swine then sheep, goats and beef. We also encourage you to attend the Premium Sale and free meal sponsored by All America Bank that will take place on Tuesday, February 4, 2020, at 6 P.M. at the Sentinel Area Activity Center.

We look forward to seeing you at these events and appreciate your support of the Sentinel FFA and 4-H chapters. Our students will be able to experience great things due to remarkable people like you.

Respectfully,
The Sentinel Jr. Livestock Show Committee

5th/6th Basketball Game on January 14 at Sweetwater -
On Tuesday, January 14, the 5th/6th Grade Basketball teams will be playing against Sweetwater at Sweetwater. The girls will begin play at 4:30. The bus will leave school around 3:00 PM. The bus will return back to Sentinel around 7:15PM. Please be at the school in front of the Sentinel Schools gym to pick up your child.

Make certain your child brings necessary items to school on game days ‚Äì socks, basketball shoes, etc. Your child may also want to bring money for the concession stand at the basketball games.
**Basketball suits will not be handed out to players until right before the game and will be given to the coaches immediately after the game. Coaches will launder suits after each game.**

**At each away game there will be a sheet of paper for you to sign if your child will not be riding the bus home. Children riding home with people other than their parents must give Mrs. Lindsey Baker, Mrs. Combs, or Mr. Graybill a signed note from their guardian during the school day.**

post_text:
This year 6th-12th grade students are only required to show up for tests they have to take. In order to be exempt a student must meet the following requirements:

Have an "A" and no more than 3 absences
a "B" and no more than 2 absences
a "C" and no more than 1 absence
*3 tardies is equal to 1 absence

A student can not have received suspension or Saturday school.

Wednesday Dec. 18th (all 6th-12th students are required to be at school in their regular classrooms until 1:30 PM)
7th hour test 6th and 7th periods (1:35-3:20)

Thursday Dec 19th
2nd hour test 1st and 2nd periods (8:35-10:20)
4th hour test 3rd and 4th periods (10:25-12:10)
6th hour test 5th and 6th periods (12:40-2:25)
7th hour = normal class

Friday Dec 20th
1st hour test 1st and 2nd periods
3rd hour test 3rd and 4th periods
5th hour test 5th and 6th periods
7th hour = normal class

Contact Mr. Graybill for more information.

4th Grade Basketball Game on Dec. 3 -
On Tuesday, December 3, the 4th Grade Basketball teams will be playing against Erick at Erick. The girls will begin play at 4:30. The bus will leave school around 3:00 PM. The bus will return back to SENTINEL in front of the gym around 7:15PM. Please be at the school in front of the gym to pick up your child.

Make certain your child brings necessary items to school on game days ‚Äì tube socks, basketball shoes, etc. Your child may also want to bring money for the concession stand at the basketball games.
**Basketball suits will not be handed out to players until right before the game and will be given to the coaches immediately after the game. Coaches will launder suits after each game.**

**At each away game there will be a sheet of paper for you to sign if your child will not be riding the bus home. Children riding home with people other than their parents must give Mrs. Combs or Mr. Goostree a signed note from their guardian during the school day.**
